ogize for the confusion and the issues you've encountered. It appears that in DevExpress version 22.2, the dxe:DateEditSettings may not be available or may have been replaced. To format a DateTime field in a dxg:GridControl using XAML, you can utilize the DisplayFormatString property within the EditSettings. Here's how you can achieve this:

xml
코드 복사
<dxg:GridControl ItemsSource="{Binding YourDataSource}">
    <dxg:GridControl.Columns>
        <!-- Other columns -->

        <!-- Time Column -->
        <dxg:GridColumn FieldName="time123" Header="Time">
            <dxg:GridColumn.EditSettings>
                <dxe:TextEditSettings DisplayFormatString="yy-MM-dd HH:mm:ss" />
            </dxg:GridColumn.EditSettings>
        </dxg:GridColumn>

    </dxg:GridControl.Columns>
</dxg:GridControl>
Explanation:

FieldName: Ensure that "time123" corresponds to the DateTime property in your data source.

DisplayFormatString: The DisplayFormatString property specifies the format in which the DateTime value will be displayed. Setting DisplayFormatString="yy-MM-dd HH:mm:ss" formats the date and time accordingly.

Additional Considerations:

Namespaces: Ensure that the necessary namespaces are declared in your XAML file:

xml
코드 복사
xmlns:dxg="http://schemas.devexpress.com/winfx/2008/xaml/grid"
xmlns:dxe="http://schemas.devexpress.com/winfx/2008/xaml/editors"
Data Binding: Verify that your ItemsSource is correctly bound to a data collection containing the time123 property of type DateTime.

Alternative Approach:

If the above method doesn't yield the desired results, consider using the Mask property along with MaskUseAsDisplayFormat:

xml
코드 복사
<dxg:GridControl ItemsSource="{Binding YourDataSource}">
    <dxg:GridControl.Columns>
        <!-- Other columns -->

        <!-- Time Column -->
        <dxg:GridColumn FieldName="time123" Header="Time">
            <dxg:GridColumn.EditSettings>
                <dxe:TextEditSettings Mask="yy-MM-dd HH:mm:ss" MaskUseAsDisplayFormat="True" />
            </dxg:GridColumn.EditSettings>
        </dxg:GridColumn>

    </dxg:GridControl.Columns>
</dxg:GridControl>
In this configuration:

Mask: The Mask property defines the input mask for the editor. Setting Mask="yy-MM-dd HH:mm:ss" specifies the desired date and time format.

MaskUseAsDisplayFormat: By setting MaskUseAsDisplayFormat="True", the mask is applied not only when editing the cell but also when displaying it, ensuring consistent formatting.

References:

For more detailed information, you can refer to the DevExpress documentation on formatting cell values: Format Cell Values